      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re right, I misunderstood how the syscall_table structure worked. I guess the options now would be to have a hashtable instead of a simple array (which I believe Jorge said that minjail does not have a hash table library) or to mimic the syscall_table data structure for previous_syscalls (which would add an extra O(n) check for every syscall policy definition in addition to the O(n) lookup that already exists in lookup_syscall to find the syscall nr info).",
      "parentUuid": "dcc2726d_2227c1bf",
      "revId": "a8041ae085c3dd8ae967e6acda1af1cfd5d5c4c5",
