      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T21:20:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, it actually would also work to just index the previous_definition table in the same way that we index the syscall_table so any time we lookup a syscall we could just get an index from that and use that number to index the previous_definition table. So we are essentially using the index of the syscall_table as the hashing function so we can make it a simple array instead but still have O(1) lookup (with the O(n) cost already being incurred in lookup_syscall).",
      "parentUuid": "16a3de76_0c583ddd",
      "revId": "a8041ae085c3dd8ae967e6acda1af1cfd5d5c4c5",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
